    <text id="B0056T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jackson asks for McDonnell to clarify the details of a contract between Punch Fox
                    and John H. Rippitoe, regarding whether or not Rippitoe agreed to teach Fox the
                    trade of brick masonry.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. &amp; A. L.</abbr>
                    <lb/>Sub <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr> Augusta &amp; Highland
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Captain">Capt.</abbr> John A.
                            McDonnell<lb/><abbr expan="Superintendent">Supt</abbr> 9th <abbr
                            expan="District">Dist</abbr><lb/>Winchester <abbr expan="Virginia"
                        >Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-04-15"><abbr expan="April">Ap</abbr> 15 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, Va</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Captain</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I respectfully forward copy (evidently imperfect) of indenture Punch Fox to John
                    H. Rippitoe. Both parties reside near Staunton. Fox claims that Rippitoe so far
                    from teaching him the trade of "brick mason" hired him out year after year as
                    farm hand and received and kept the whole amount of such hire.</p>

                <p>Both in default to teach him the trade of "brick mason" &amp; settlement
                    subsequent to the expiration of apprenticeship Fox claims that Rippetoe has
                    defrauded him.</p>

                <p>Can you have the copy enclosed compared with the original on record in Nelson
                    County and the omission between the words "Punch Fox" and "in the craft"
                    &amp;c supplied or correct copy made.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <abbr expan="Your">Yr</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="obedient">obt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="servant">servt</abbr>
                    </salute>
                    <signed><abbr expan="Thomas">Thos.</abbr> P. Jackson <lb/><abbr
                            expan="Assistant Superintendent">Asst Supt</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
